author: @iammdla
text:
Dear Jimin,

I hope that when you read this letter, you are well, happy, and full of energy. I want you to know that your smile and your talent brighten my life every day. You are a constant inspiration to me, not only because of your music and art but also because of the humble, kind, and hardworking person you are.

Thank you for coming into my life during difficult times and for healing my wounds with your voice and presence. Your effort and dedication motivate me to be better and never give up. I admire how you always give your best, even when you push yourself hard, and that teaches me to fight for my dreams with the same passion.

I wouldnâ€™t change anything about you because every part of who you are is perfect and unique. Thank you for existing and for being a beacon of light for me and millions of people. Even though I canâ€™t see you in person, I will always be supporting you and celebrating your achievements from afar.

With all my love and admiration,

author: @Smartandlonely
text:
Dear Jimin, Jiminie, Jiminshi, Chim Chim, Baby Mochi and etc; 

I wanted to write something about you, with the hope that one day you will read what I wrote. 

Each member is very precious, their individual talents are indisputable. But even RM has said many times that the person who attracted the most attention during BTSÂ  first stage debut was you Jiminie. You made BTS more well-known. You have always been at an important place for BTS with your dance breaks and appearance in the most important parts of the songs. (No more dreams, we are bulletproof, N.O., fire, blood sweat and tears, not today, black swan...)Â  In later periods, you have always been the most notable member with your unique dances, visual and courage. 

What I want to tell you is that we didn't love you just because of your beautiful voice. We loved you for your unique dancing talent, which no one else has, which has always enabled you to be at the top of the "best kpop dancers ever" lists. 

We loved you for your eye-catching stage performances and perfect stage presence. 

We loved you for your fun personality that fills everywhere you enter with joy, your perfect smile that is out of this world, and your laughter that warms our hearts. 

We loved you because you thought about everyone (A.R.M.Y, members, family, friends...) more than yourself. We loved you because we know how humble and helpful you are. 

All we want from you is that ; you love yourself as much as we love you. It makes us very sad that you have been so insecure about yourself and always blamed yourself just because of your voice for years. Please know that you are not just about your vocal talent. 

I hope you take care of yourself in the military and return to your fans waiting for you as soon as possible. 

I love you very much my dear Jiminie â¤ï¸
